Key Match Events: Austin Riley hit a two-run homer in the first inning to open the scoring
Spencer Strider recorded 9 strikeouts, bringing his total to 424 strikeouts in his first 50 career starts, the most since 1893
Post-Match Reflections: The Braves puffed on their championship cigars, showered each other with bubbly, shot-gunned beers and danced in alcohol puddles
Kirby Yates struck out Brandon Marsh to end the game and the players danced in a mob near the mound as Phillies fans booed them off the field
Ronald Acuña Jr. responded to booing fans by raising both arms and signaling with his hands to bring it on
Brian Snitker said, ‘Now the real party starts’
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Braves clinched their sixth straight NL East title
The Braves have seemingly made winning the East a rite of September since the 1990s
The Braves have gone nearly wire-to-wire in the 2023 season
The Braves took special satisfaction in clinching on the same Citizens Bank Park field where the Phillies eliminated them last October in the NL Division Series
The Phillies lead the NL wild card and the teams could face each other in October
Others: The Braves star Ronald Acuña Jr. went 0-4 against Phillies pitching
Starter Spencer Strider also reached a milestone with his nine strikeouts
